   &UR; WASHINGTON _ (Moved in ``w'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GORE-CAMPAIGN _ President Clinton is concerned that Vice
President Al Gore's campaign to succeed him seems to be
floundering, according to several people close to the president.
They say Clinton has personally coached Gore on how to loosen up
and appear less remote and rigid on the campaign trail. By Richard
L. Berke.
</P>
<P>
   JUVENILE-CRIME-ASSESS _ From Arkansas to Colorado, most
shootings produce much more sound and fury than and political or
legislative action. A look at the political power of the NRA, and
the attempts by Republicans to turn the focus elsewhere. By Alison
Mitchell.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-DUKE-RESEARCH (Durham, N.C.) _ More and more patients are
getting care through participation in research experiments or
clinical trials. What happens to them, and the researchers, when
the government steps in and halts the program, as it did this week
at Duke University? By Philip J. Hilts.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-CHROMOSOME-LOOPS (Undated) _ Researchers have long wondered
why a cell's ``suicide mechanism,'' triggered by breaks in DNA, is
not activated by the endings of chromosomes. Now they know: the
ends of chromosomes are tied up in a elegant little loop. By
Nicholas Wade.
</P>
