   &UR; Moved as BC-NATO-MURPHY'S-LAW-600&AMP;add-INDEPENDENT-NYTSF &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE ENEMY WITHIN: NATO TURNS TO SELF-CRITICISM &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; By STEPHEN CASTLE, The Independent of London &LR;  &QC; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BRUSSELS _ The question was serious, but the answer came back
with a full, shoulder-heaving laugh.
</P>
<P>
   No, replied the senior NATO diplomat, the alliance had not made
contact with dissident elements in Belgrade: ``Quite frankly,'' he
said, ``we are not that good.''
</P>
<P>
   Almost seven weeks into the Balkans bombing campaign a sudden
outburst of frankness _ and soul-searching _ has struck NATO's
headquarters in Brussels... &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (NOTE: Article can stand in 725; total uncut version is 1,050
words) &LR;  &QC;
</P>
