<P>
   CANBERRA _ A year ago, Australians were being told to batten
down the hatches. The economic turmoil sweeping Asia was expected
to turn south and engulf a country whose economy has been
notoriously prone to boom-bust cycles.
</P>
<P>
   Australia sells about 60 percent of its exports to Asia, many of
