new markets.
</P>
<P>
   Clothing factories, once heavily protected, have gone out of
business, whereas industries with higher added value, such as
medical equipment and car parts, have prospered.
</P>
<P>
   When the Asian turmoil began in 1997, many Australian producers
looked elsewhere to sell. Last year, Australia's exports to Europe
