<SLUG> BC-RAC-LUKAS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LUKAS, TRAINER OF WINNERS, EYES THE PREAKNESS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By MATT GRAVES  
 c.1999 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   BALTIMORE _ D. Wayne Lukas has trained winners of 11 Triple
Crown races in a Hall of Fame career, but he's still waiting for
that exceptional 3-year-old who can win all of them in the span of
six weeks.
</P>
<P>
   Lukas, who will be enshrined in the Racing Hall of Fame in
Saratoga Springs, N.Y., in August, has another opportunity with
Charismatic in Saturday's 124th running of the Preakness at Pimlico
Race Course, the second jewel in the Triple Crown.
</P>
<P>
   Lukas has trained four Kentucky Derby winners, four Preakness
winners and three Belmont winners, but not once has he gone to the
final leg of thoroughbred heaven with a chance to win the Triple
Crown.
</P>
<P>
   ``I got the three races in a row; I just can't get them with the
same horse,'' said Lukas, referring to his sweep of the 1995 Triple
Crown events with Thunder Gulch (Derby, Belmont) and Timber Country
(Preakness). ``One of these years, that's gonna fall in place.
Maybe this year.''
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic would be the least likely Triple Crown winner in
history, having come out of the claiming ranks to stun the Kentucky
Derby field at odds of 31-1, but Lukas said it's not beyond the
realm of possibility.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel good about this horse in the second leg because he's
really peaked at the right time,'' Lukas said. ``I'm sure there'll
be people who will digest this and say there's too many outs (15
starts) and he's got to bounce, but don't count on that. He's doing
pretty good.''
</P>
<P>
   Charismatic also has Preakness success in his bloodlines. His
sire, Summer Squall, won the race in 1990. Charismatic's
grandfather, Northern Dancer, won the 1964 Preakness.
</P>
<P>
   Still, Pimlico oddsmaker Clem Florio isn't convinced Charismatic
has the goods, making the Derby winner the third choice in the
expected field of 12 at revised odds of 5-1. He was originally
listed as fourth choice.
</P>
<P>
   Lukas said that while it's true Charismatic enjoyed a smooth
ride in the Derby _ several other horses were jostled in the
crowded field _ he had to overcome the difficult 16th post position
and was never able to run close to the rail, making his neck
victory over Menifee all the more impressive.
</P>
<P>
   ``We came from an outside hole, we were wide into the first
turn, wide down the backstretch and wide on the far turn,'' Lukas
said. ``The only thing we didn't do was (check), and that was by
design. I told my riders, do anything, but don't start-and-stop
because I don't know if we're good enough to overcome that.''Lukas'
horses finished 1-3 in the Derby, with Cat Thief taking the show
position behind the late-charging Menifee, the likely post-time
favorite in the Preakness.
</P>
<P>
   ``Both of my riders rode hellacious races in light of what you
saw,'' Lukas said, praising winner Chris Antley and Cat Thief's
Mike Smith. ``It's a great tribute to both Chris and Mike.''
</P>
<P>
   The Derby marked the first time Charismatic had put together
back-to-back wins. He won the Lexington only 13 days before the
Derby upset. Cat Thief has been consistent in big races, but hasn't
won any of them this year.
</P>
<P>
   ``I expect Cat Thief to keep everything honest again,'' Lukas
said of Charismatic's front-running stablemate. ``It wouldn't
surprise me to see him win this race. He's got the right running
style for it.''
</P>
<P>
   A victory by Cat Thief would put Lukas in the same position he
was in four years ago _ having saddled different winners of the
first two legs of the Triple Crown. That year was part of an
unprecedented string in which Lukas horses won six consecutive
Triple Crown races.
</P>
<P>
   Now 63, Lukas seems confident he still has time to accomplish
what hasn't been done since 1978 by colleague Laz Barrera with
Affirmed _ win a Triple Crown.``We'll just keep coming back,'' he
said, ``until it falls in place for us.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
