<P>
   KOSOVO-STRIKES _ WASHINGTON _ The latest Friday on the U.S.-led
NATO bombing campaign against Yugoslavia. The Tanjug
state-controlled news agency, reported 100 civilians in a column of
500 ethnic Albanian refugees heading toward the Albanian border
were killed in a NATO aerial attack. The allies said they could not
immediately confirm or deny the report. Meanwhile, Apache attack
