   ISRAEL-VOTE _ El Al (the Israeli Airline) is offering charter
flights at cut rates, and several Israeli political parties are
sponsoring trips to Israel to bring back Israelis living in America
so they can vote in the May 17 election. Election turnout is
already about 80 percent in Israel and the last election was
decided by less than 30,000 votes of about 2 million cast. There
are around 100,000 Israelis living in America; none can vote by
mail except diplomats so the effort to get them back is intense. We
will speak to at least one Israeli living in Boca Raton about why
he feels it is important to go back, as well as Israeli political
analysts and political organizers in the Miami area. (Belkin, Palm
