humans are being used in a new test that can pinpoint contaminated
food in eight hours _ compared with the two to three days it
currently takes to grow colonies of bacteria from samples.
Scientists hope to make it available commercially soon. Meanwhile,
the Japanese are marketing another home food-poisoning kit although
it picks up harmless dead bacteria as well as live ones. By Andy
Coghlan. 600 words. (slugged:
BC-DANGEROUS-BACTERIA-(NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF) &QL;
