insects and help plants boost seed production in exchange for
dollops of sugary nectar. Scientists have long known that ants
provide this service for plants, but this is the first evidence
that spiders can also interact with plants in this way. By Matt
Walker. 350 words. (slugged:
BC-PLANT-PEST-CONTROL-NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF) &QL; 
