<P>
   ISRAELI-ELECTIONS (Jerusalem) _ A special report on Monday's
elections. The mainbar looks at Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
going on the defensive in the campaign's closing days and concludes
that his is now a campaign of quiet desperation, down nearly 10
points in the polls. From the sidelines, watching intently, is his
nemesis, Yasser Arafat. But don't count the conservative prime
minister out yet. By DEBORAH HORAN.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-RUSSIANS _ This sidebar looks at Israel's new bloc of
swing voters who seem to be breaking for Barak, the opposition
leader of the dovish Labor Party. But the question is: Will they
turn out? By DEBORHAH HORAN.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-MULTIPARTIES _ This sidebar looks at the many small
parties that populate the Israeli political galaxy. By DEBORAH
HORAN.
