<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ Once the furor subsides over
NATO's accidental bombing of the Chinese Embassy in Belgrade and
peace negotiations resume, flexibility will be the key to success.
That's the way peace accords usually are achieved. It's rare that
the United States, with all its vast power, gets all it wants at
the peace table. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON. (Filed Wednesday.)
