<SLUG> BC-CAR-NASCAR-ADVANCE15-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Wallace, Andretti fastest in practice
 &HT;    By Al Levine
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   RICHMOND, Va. - How's this for Excitement? Rain has forced
NASCAR's Winston Cup drivers into a one-day show for tonight's
Pontiac Excitement 400.
</P>
<P>
   They'll practice at 10:30 this morning, qualify for starting
positions at 12:30 this afternoon, practice again at 2 and run the
Pontiac 400 tonight at 7:40 at Richmond International Raceway.
</P>
<P>
   Thursday's qualifying round and a morning practice session were
rained out. Drivers managed to squeeze in a 90-minute practice,
which only confirmed what everyone already knows: Rusty Wallace and
John Andretti have the fastest cars right now on short tracks. Each
has won a short track race this season and Wallace has led 60
percent of the laps (602 of 1000) raced on short tracks this
season.
</P>
<P>
   Wallace, in a Ford, circled the three-quarter-mile asphalt track
in 126.292 mph (21.379 seconds) and Andretti, in a Pontiac, was
second-fastest at 125.986 mph. Ken Schrader (sixth-fastest) had the
fastest Chevrolet at 125.605.
</P>
<P>
   The big practice surprises were Jeff Gordon's 15th-fastest time
of 124.890 mph and Dale Earnhardt, at 122.844 mph, the 43rd fastest
among 46 cars. Only Derrike Cope was slower than Tucker's Buckshot
Jones (122.272 mph).
</P>
<P>
   Jeff Burton leads the points race by 55 over Dale Jarrett. There
have been seven different winners in the first 10 races this
season.
</P>
<P>
   Gordon won the pole for last year's race but was eliminated when
Wallace brushed his car exiting turn two and Gordon's No. 24
Chevrolet ended up in the wall. Terry Labonte survived four caution
periods in the final 27 laps to win the race.
</P>
<P>
   Rain began wreaking havoc on the weekend schedule Thursday night
when daylong threatening skies opened up 68 laps into the 150-lap
NASCAR Featherlite Modified race.
</P>
<P>
   The foul weather continued until 4 p.m. Friday. By then,
second-round qualifying for the Hardees 250 Busch race had been
scrubbed as well as Friday evening's Cup qualifying round.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
