<SLUG> BC-BKN-PIPPEN-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DWI CHARGES AGAINST HOUSTON'S PIPPEN DROPPED 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (Attn: Calif., Ill.) 
 
By JERRY URBAN 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON _ Charges of driving while intoxicated against Houston
Rockets forward Scottie Pippen were dropped Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Pippen's attorney, Rusty Hardin, said the charges were dismissed
after the district attorney's office determined there was
insufficient evidence that Pippen, 33, was intoxicated.
</P>
<P>
   The motion to dismiss was accepted Friday in the Harris County
Criminal Court-at-Law of Judge Sherman Ross. A representative of
the district attorney's office could not be reached late Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Police stopped Pippen's Mercedes at 1:20 a.m. April 22 after he
allegedly passed traffic stopped for a red light in downtown
Houston.
</P>
<P>
   Police say Pippen failed a field sobriety test and was arrested.
Authorities say he was later videotaped and refused to take a
Breathalyzer test.
</P>
<P>
   Pippen was charged with misdemeanor DWI. He was released after
posting a $500 bail.
</P>
<P>
   Patrons of the Jones Bar in Houston said Pippen was there after
an April 21 game, with teammates Charles Barkley and Matt Maloney.
The Rockets had lost 109-95 to the Dallas Mavericks in Compaq
Center, with Pippen scoring four points.
</P>
<P>
   Pippen appeared in court briefly April 30 and his next court was
set for May 26.
</P>
<P>
   After 11 years with the six-time NBA champion Chicago Bulls,
Pippen was traded to the Rockets in January. The team signed him to
a five-year, $67 million contract.
</P>
<P>
   Pippen was arrested in Chicago in January 1994 after a police
officer checking on his illegally parked car noticed a loaded
.380-caliber semiautomatic handgun inside. The charge was dismissed
when a judge ruled the officer had no probable cause to look in the
car.
</P>
<P>
   Pippen was charged with misdemeanor domestic battery in May
1995, after being accused of grabbing his fiancee, Yvette Deleone,
and shoving her. The case was dismissed when Deleone declined to
testify.
</P>
<P>
   Pippen scored 37 points in a 102-88 win Thursday night over the
Los Angeles Lakers in an NBA playoff game. The Rockets trail the
Lakers 2-1 in the best-of-fives series.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
